
Overview of noun pigment

The noun pigment has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) pigment -- (dry coloring material (especially a powder to be mixed with a liquid to produce paint, etc.))
2. pigment -- (any substance whose presence in plant or animal tissues produces a characteristic color)
3. paint, pigment -- (a substance used as a coating to protect or decorate a surface (especially a mixture of pigment suspended in a liquid); dries to form a hard coating; "artists use `paint' and `pigment' interchangeably")

Overview of verb pigment

The verb pigment has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. pigment -- (acquire pigment; become colored or imbued)
2. pigment -- (color or dye with a pigment; "pigment a photograph")
